<p>Fixing the <code v-pre>NoUniqueBeanDefinitionException</code>:</p>
<p>When we run the above code, Spring will throw a <code v-pre>NoUniqueBeanDefinitionException</code> because it finds two beans (<code v-pre>Airtel</code> and <code v-pre>Jio</code>) of type <code v-pre>Sim</code>. To resolve this, we need to specify which bean to inject.</p>
<ol>
<li>Use <code v-pre>@Primary</code> Annotation: Mark one of the beans as the primary bean.</li>
</ol>
