<h2 id="spel" tabindex="-1"><a class="header-anchor" href="#spel"><span>SpEL</span></a></h2>
<p>Spring Expression Language (SpEL) is a feature in the Spring Framework used to evaluate expressions and manipulate objects <strong>at runtime</strong>. It helps in <strong>dynamically configuring beans</strong>, accessing properties, and invoking methods within Spring applications.</p>
<h3 id="syntax" tabindex="-1"><a class="header-anchor" href="#syntax"><span>Syntax</span></a></h3>
<ul>
<li><code v-pre>#{...}</code>: SpEL expression.</li>
<li><code v-pre>${...}</code>: Property placeholder.</li>
</ul>
